    "code": "def solve(n, m):\n    if n > m:\n        return 0\n    L = m + 1\n    # find min n^p for p >= L\n    # try each bit position where we can \"branch\"\n    best = float('inf')\n    # go bit by bit\n    bits = 30\n    for i in range(bits, -1, -1):\n        # consider setting bit i of p to be 1 when n's bit i is 0 (or vice versa)\n        # making p > current prefix of L at bit i, then minimize remaining bits = match n\n        mask = (1 << (i+1)) - 1\n        prefix_L = L >> (i+1) << (i+1)  # upper bits of L\n        # if upper bits of p match L, and bit i of p > bit i of L\n        # then lower bits can be anything -> set to match n\n        bit_L = (L >> i) & 1\n        # set bit i of p to be > bit_L (i.e., 1 when bit_L=0)\n        if bit_L == 0:\n            p_candidate = prefix_L | (1 << i) | (n & ((1 << i) - 1))\n            best = min(best, n ^ p_candidate)\n    # also check p = L itself... already covered if we match all bits\n    best = min(best, n ^ L) # not always valid but L >= L\n    return best",
